It's important to remember the massive amounts of earth and labor abuses that go into the creation of modern technologies. These technologies are punctualized, that is, turned into a simple systems of inputs and outputs that distracts from or hides the internalities of the technology (meant abstractly and literally: both the internal circuitry and material usage, and the exterior mineral extraction, labor practices, supply chains, etc.).
